Michelle Jackson, the ex-wife of Music promoter Don Jazzy, has recalled their time together with nostalgia. The US-based Nigerian, in an interview with Pulse podcasts, said being married to the music producer was good despite occasional arguments and misunderstandings. She said they defied societal expectation that the union was bound to fail because if their young ages. According to her: ”We were so carefree and happy, I don’t think we had so much baggage that maybe I would have now.   I may die soon, says Elon Musk     How to become a good cross dresser, by Bobrisky     I’m not bi-s3xual, says ex-BBNaija’s Emmanuel   “It was just fun and of course every relationship has its ups and downs. We’d probably fight a while and then we would be cool again. “Honestly I know that at that particular age, there were so many things that could have gone wrong, but for the most part of our marriage a lot of things went right and we were just cool, we were easy. “He’s very down to earth, very cool. We flowed mehn, we flowed.”